                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21864",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tbuehl",
                        "name": "tbuehl",
                        "displayName": "Torsten B\u00fchl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello Matthew,\n\nI am working at a project right now and want to change to Zend_Form from my own Form Implementation. How can I implement this feature quick in the class? I tried to copy & paste your code but it's not working. There is no Element Decorator. \n\nBest, Torsten",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tbuehl",
                        "name": "tbuehl",
                        "displayName": "Torsten B\u00fchl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-05-21T05:21:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-05-21T05:21:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24368",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gog",
                        "name": "gog",
                        "displayName": "Goran Juric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Haven't tried it, but I think you should be able to do something like this:\n\nCreate a view helper:\n\n[code]\n<table>\n    <tr>\n        <td><?= $this->element->getLabel() ?><\/td>\n        <td>\n            <?= $this->element->render() ?>\n            <?= $this->element->getDescription() ?>\n            <?= $this->element->getErrors() ?>\n        <\/td>\n    <\/tr>\n[\/code]\n\nand add it to the element (or extend Zend_Form and set this to all elements) via a ViewScript decorator.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gog",
                        "name": "gog",
                        "displayName": "Goran Juric",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-08T12:29:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-08T12:29:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24372",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Goran -- not quite what the reporter is looking for. The idea is to be able to render an individual decorator at a time, not just the metadata.",
